Product Requirements Document (PRD): Sanctions & Compliance API
1. Executive Summary
Product Name: AML Check API (Working Title)
Objective: Provide a fast, reliable, and easy-to-integrate REST API for global and Pan-African Fintechs, Crypto exchanges, and Neobanks to screen users against global and local African watchlists.
Target Audience: Developers and compliance officers at B2B fintechs, specifically targeting the African ecosystem (Nigeria, Kenya, South Africa).
Value Proposition: Eliminate engineering overhead spent parsing messy global files and scraping local African PDFs. One /screen endpoint with built-in fuzzy matching to ensure compliance across multiple jurisdictions.

2. Core Problem & Solution
The Problem
Regulatory Burden: Institutions are legally barred from transacting with entities on lists like OFAC (US), UN, and local lists like Nigeria’s NFIU/CBN directives.
Data Quality: Sources are fragmented and messy (legacy XML, massive CSVs, and non-standardized PDFs requiring OCR).
Matching Complexity: "Exact match" search is ineffective. Identifying "Jon Doe" against "John Doe" requires complex fuzzy-search engineering.
The Solution
A fully managed API that:
Ingests & Normalizes: Daily automated pulls from top global and African government sources into a unified, clean database.
Fuzzy Searching: A JSON-based endpoint returning a match probability score based on names and metadata.
Audit Logs: Secure transaction history providing "Proof of Diligence" for regulatory audits.

3. Product Requirements & Features
V1 Features (MVP)
Single Search Endpoint: POST /v1/screen
Input: Name (Individual/Company), Country, Date of Birth (Optional).
Output: Match Score (0−100%), Matched Entity Details, Source List, and Source Links.
Fuzzy Matching Algorithm: Handles misspellings, missing middle names, and phonetic similarities (e.g., Stephen vs. Steven).
Automated Daily Ingestion: Nightly workers to parse/normalize US OFAC, UK HMT, UN, Nigeria NFIU, and Nigeria CBN/EFCC (including PDF OCR).
Developer Portal: Simple dashboard for API key management and usage tracking.
Tiered Rate Limiting: Free (100 req/mo) vs. Pro (10,000 req/mo) tiers.
V2 Features (Roadmap)
Webhooks: Proactive alerts when an existing customer is added to a list post-onboarding.
PEP Verification: Integration of Politically Exposed Persons (PEP) data.
Compliance Dashboard: UI for manual review and "False Positive" flagging.

4. Technical Architecture
Architecture Overview
Ingestion Layer: Nightly cron jobs pulling XML/CSV and PDF documents from global and African government servers.
Normalization Layer: Standardizes date formats, name splitting, and column mapping.
Search Index: Optimized database built specifically for high-speed fuzzy-text matching.
API Gateway: Stateless backend for authentication, querying, and logging.
MVP Data Sources
Global:
US OFAC: Specially Designated Nationals (SDN) List.
UN Consolidated List: UN Security Council sanctions.
UK HMT: HM Treasury Financial Sanctions Targets.
African/Nigerian:
NFIU: Sanctions for terrorism financing, fraud, and money laundering.
CBN Directives: Circulars and lists of frozen accounts (via PDF OCR/Scraping).
EFCC Wanted List: Active wanted list for fraud and financial crimes.

